<h1>@HI{{toha}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> <em>phrase</em> <strong>@HI{{toha}}</strong>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{toha}}</strong> indicates a word or phrase that is being defined.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      UN<strong>@HI{{toha}}</strong>,@KJ{{country^take*along}}@HI{{nokotodesu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      "UN" refers to the United Nations.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{toha}}</strong> is used between two clauses that are opposed in meaning, the first clause representing a concession to the second.
In this case it usually appears in the form <strong>@HI{{tohaie}}</strong>. The meaning is "though" or "even though".

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{springtime}}<strong>tohaie</strong>mada@KJ{{cold}}i.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Even though it's spiring, it's still cold.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

